					<p>I agree we Linux users should improve our security, for different reasons. There are many techinques nowadays to sandbox our apps in case they have vulnerabilities. Installing an antivirus is obsolete. The antivirus are innefective against the polymorphic viruses of the 21st century. And if you don&#8217;t want to infect windows users, all you have to do is delete the autorun.inf files that your usb disks gets whenever you plug it in a windows box.</p>
