					<p>One has  to really try to get a virus on Linux.  If you use safe repositories (which can be checked with very little effort), don&#8217;t run as root, install and use your firewall,  and install software from untrusted sources, I defy you to become infected!  The number of Linux and Mac viruses in the wild are still unbelievably tiny compared to Windows.  Sorry, this is FUD.</p>
