					<p>Currently, Linux Desktops are more secure. They are not common, and Linux is usually open source. Which means that malware for Linux is harder to develop. Yet, I do not say linux is insecure. Yes, I am using antivirus on Linux. However, I do not use Sophos, and I like it that way. Plus, I am backing up my data.</p>
