				<div class="comment-content post-content" itemprop="text">
					<p>Market share has a lot to do with how big a target a OS is. Malware has a much better chance of succeeding on a bigger market platform then on say a small one like Linux desktop. The focus would obviously be on Windows and cross over malware that affects different OS&#8217;s is just a bonus that sometimes happens with a exploit that can happen on multiple OS&#8217;s. My question has always been to a Linux or Mac OS user who claims they are malware immune. Exactly, how do you know that for sure, since you don&#8217;t use any security applications? Is this just based on assumption? Lot of malware works in the background with little or no notable issues that the end user would detect.</p>
